        • [ - ] vikasjoshi9617 - member since 19-Nov-14

          They say that Sporting is best club in Portugal that develops youngsters. But how many young portuguese players are getting chance? The reason behind Portugals failure at international stage is because once their players are developed in Portuguese league, they ddin't move to try something different. Example Moutinho took too long time to transfer to top 5 league club. Portugal FA should think about this. They should set rule something like 5/6 regional players and remaining foreign players. I don't want to hurt people that love this league but I really don't think there is enough competition in league. Always Benfica or Porto. But future looks bright for Portugal. Some of young players have already moved to top 5 league clubs and really doing well. Bruno,Lopes,Vezo, Gomes,Raphael, Bruma. Even some players like Neves,Guedes are doing well. It seems Portugal have bright future in terms of Attack and Midfield. They must focus on developing defence and goalkeepers for future.

        • [ - ] libero - member since 10-Apr-14

          @vikasjoshi9617 First of all, yes: Sporting is well-known for having a fabulous academy like Ajax, Lyon and Barcelona. Second, Moutinho's move is debatable: comparing Monaco to Porto I wouldn't say he's moving to the next level.Third, I think you're right in some points. Portugal lives for youngsters mainly and they're well-known for develop them. But they mostly live for foreign (south-american mainly)youngsters. That's the reason behind Portugal's failure at international (national team!) stage: there's been a lack of investiment on the portuguese players so national team doesn't have much option and often call up unfitted players. But the future sure looks promising. Also, Portuguese league lacks as much competition as Spanish: you have Real Madrid and Barcelona (Porto and Benfica) and not much title contenders after that. Atltico appears once in awhile (Sporting), Valencia too (Braga) you have teams that fight for Europa League (Vit. Guimares, Estoril) and the rest struggle.
